{
  "text": "eSF]fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) was prepared by the cyclotron staff of the Mount Sinai Medical Center, using the nucleophilic reaction [CITATION_1] , modified to produce multimillicurie doses (Vora et aI., 1985) . Sub jects arrived 1 h prior to commencement of PET scanning (performed between 11:00 a.m. and 4:00 p.m.). Subjects fasted for a minimum period of 3 h prior to the study and had not smoked cigarettes or taken any medication, alco hol, coffee, or tea on the day of the study.",
